<!-- Props and states
-----------------

what is Props?
---------------
* Props stand for "properties." they are ready_only components. it is an object which stores the value of attributes of a tag and work similar to the HTML attributes. 
* Props are immutable. they cannot be changed. they are set by the parent and they are fixed throughout the lifetime of a component.
* functional components receive props as parameters.
* props play a crucial role in creating dynamic and reusable components by allowing them to be configured with different data based on their usage within the application.

how Props work?
----------------
* Parent component sends data as props.
* child component receives props as an arguement.
* we use props.name, props.age to access the data.
pro tip:- use meaningful names for props to make your code easier to read and understand. 
 
Props Destucting
-----------------------
Props destructing in React functional components is a common pattern that allows youu to extract values directly
from the props object,making your code cleaner and easier to read.



React State 
* State is used to store and manage data inside a components.
* when state changes the UI updates automatically.
Why State ?
* Makes component intractive 
* UI updates based on data change
* Handles dynamic data(forms,counters,boggles,etc)
* inproves ue experience.
 useState()Hook
 * The useState hook is a built-in React hook that allows functional components to manage stateful data without using class components.
 It return a pair of values:the current state and a function to update that state.useState enables functional components to have their oen state
 ,making tem more powerfull and flexible.

 Syntax:
 const[state,setState]=useState(value for variable)
 * useState(): is simple predefined javascript function which is coming for next react library.
 * useState will be return one array which contains exaactly two elements i,e state,setState.
 * First element is a state variable and second element is a function(setter function).
 * State a special variable in react where we can store any tye of data.
 example:
 let[state,setState]=useState(0)
 let[state,setState]=useState("Bharath)
 let[state,setState]=useState(([name:'raj",age:27]))
 let[state,setState]=useState(true)
 let[state,setState]=useState([10,20,30,50])

